info.name: Find a Dog for Me
info.description:
## Introduction

This RESTful API is provided by the backend server and consumed by the frontend server for use in supplying findadogfor.me with dynamic information about models.

## Overview

The models that this API provides are **"shelters", "dogs", "breeds",** and **"activities"**. API calls for obtaining relevant attributes, connections, and media about and between these models are included.

The RESTful API sources for this API include:
* Petfinder API
* TheDog API
* Dog API
* Eventbrite API
* Meetup API
* National Parks API

These sources are subject to change based on availability of data.

## Authentication

All API calls must be accompanied by a bearer token.

## Status Codes

* **200: Request Succeeded** 
	* Request has succeeded!
* **404: Not Found** 
    * Server cannot find the resource you're trying to access.
* **500: Internal Server Error**
	* Server encountered unexpected condition that prevented it from fulfilling the request.
	* If this happens, please let us know!

## Rate Limit

Currently, no rate limit exists with this API.

item.name: Shelters

query.description: (Optional) The shelter for which you'd like specific data for.
(Optional) The page of results you'd like

request.description:
Returns a list of shelter items matching the specified criteria.

If no parameters are provided, returns a list of all shelter items, paginated.

Parameters:

id - (Optional) The shelter for which you'd like specific data for.

page - (Optional) The page of results you'd like

Return type:
```
dict {
	objects: [
		shelter_dict_1,
		...
		shelter_dict_12
	],
	page: number
}
```

query.description: (Required) The shelter id for which you want to find nearby activities
(Optional) The range (in degrees) from the shelter in which you want to find nearby activities.
(Optional) The current page (12 activities per page) of nearby activity information to request.

request.description:
Returns a list of activity items found near a specific shelter, paginated.

"id" is a required parameter.

Parameters: 

id - (Required) The shelter id for which you want to find nearby activities

range - (Optional) The range (in degrees) from the shelter in which you want to find nearby activities.

page - (Optional) The current page (12 activities per page) of nearby activity information to request.

Return type:
```
dict {
	objects: [
		activity_dict_1,
		...
		activity_dict_12
	],
	page: number
}
```

request.description:
Returns a list of shelters that match specfic filters. Can also use this method to sort results in a specific order.


Parameters: 

city_filter - (Optional) The city in which you'd like to find shelters.

zipcode_filter - (Optional) The zipcode in which you'd like to find shelters. 

phone_filter - (Optional) The area code in which you'd like to filter shelter phone numbers by. Not all shelters have phone numbers associated with them, so use the above two filters as much as you can to narrow down the results, before resorting to this.

search_param - (Optional) A string to search for in the shelter list. 

sort_param - (Optional) Possible sorts include "alphabetical", "reverse_alphabetical", "zipcode", and "reverse_zipcode"

page_num - (Optional) The page of results you'd like.


Return type:
```
dict {
	objects: [
		shelter_dict_1,
		...
		shelter_dict_12
	],
	page: number
}
```

API calls related to the Shelter model.

Shelter Model:
```
dict {
	id: string,
	name: string,
	latitude: number,
	longitude: number,
	city: string,
	state: string,
	zipcode: number,
	phone: string, 
	address: string,
}
```

request.description:
Returns a list of dog items matching the specified criteria.

If no parameters are provided, returns a list of all dog items, paginated.

Parameters:

id - (Optional) The id of the dog you'd like information about.

page - (Optional) The current page (12 dogs per page) of dog information.
Return type:
```
dict {
	objects: [
		dog_dict_1,
		...
		doct_dict_12
	],
	page: number
}
```

{
    "age": "Adult",
    "breed": "border terrier",
    "description": "This little lady is fun to be around. She can come across a bit rough play and bossy to others. She needs a firm. NO!!! to find her place in a pack. She plays well with the cats and her foster crew but she will not back down if charged!! She does bark some and at times not sure what she barks out so may not be a good apartment dog if left alone. She loves her kennel and will go right in, even at night. She can be a bit protective or her human even with kids but she is slowly learning. She can not be the ruler of the home and needs an alpha!. Rides well in a car too but prefers to be in you lap asleep. 

Est DOB:  09/01/13
Current weight:  10 pounds

IF you are ready to adopt NOW, we can normally arrange transport to get the dog there within 1 to 2 weeks.  

We usually answer all emails back within 48 hours. Please watch your spam folders as an application will be attached and this sometimes places it in there. 

Also not all dogs listed will make the trip. Only serious adoption inquires will be coming. 

HIS/HER adoption fee is $550 USD and that will pay for TRANSPORT, all his/her shots up to date, neutered/spayed, microchip and rabies.

Please e-mail MuttsAndMeows@Mail.com for an adoption application and learn how to pre-adopt. 

For those of you who want/need to meet a dog before adopting,  we will be coming in April.  We can not guarantee that this dog will not be adopted before then.  If you would like to get the dog sooner than April, we will give you as much info as we can about the dog so you can make an informed decision.

This dog will be at Portland/Beaverton and Vancouver, WA early April (see dates below)	
EMAIL for PRE-ADOPTION!!! 

April 11, 12  2019  (Thursday and Friday)
Portland Location: 
Petsmart 
12375 SW Walker Rd
Beaverton, OR 97005

April 13  2019  (Saturday)
Vancouver, WA Location: 
Petsmart 
7603 NE Vancouver Plaza Dr, 
Vancouver, WA 98662

Like us on Facebook - search Mutts & Meows - and help even more pets find loving homes.

request.description:
Returns a list of activity objects that would be suitable for the dog within the specified range, paginated.

'id' is required as a parameter.

Parameters:

id - (Required) The ID of the dog.

range - (Optional) The range (in degrees) from the shelter the dog is hosted at in which you want to find suitable activities. Defaults to 0.5 degrees if no range is provided.

page - (Optional) The current page (12 activities per page) of activity information.


Return type:
```
dict {
	objects: [
		activity_dict_1,
		...
		activity_dict_12
	],
	page: number
}
```

request.description:
Returns a list of dogs that match specfic filters. Can also use this method to sort results in a specific order.

Parameters:

breed_filter - (Optional) The specific breed that you'd like to search for. 
 
age_filter - (Optional) The age that you'd like to filter by. "Adult", "Young", "Baby", and "Senior" are valid inputs. 

size_filter - (Optional) The size of the dog you'd liko te filter by. "S", "M", "L", and "XL" are valid inputs.

search_param - (Optional) A string to search for in the dog list. 

sort_param - (Optional) Possible sorts include "alphabetical", "reverse_alphabetical", "size", and "reverse_size".

page_num - (Optional) The page of results you'd like.

Return type:
```
dict {
	objects: [
		dog_dict_1,
		...
		doct_dict_12
	],
	page: number
}
```

item.description:
API calls related to the Dog model.

Dog Model:
```
dict {
	id: string,
	shelter_id: string
	name: string,
	breed: string,
	age: string,
	size: string,
	sex: string,
	description: string,
	image_1: string,
	image_2: string,
	image_3: string,
	image_4: string,
}
```

item.name: Breeds

request.description:
Returns a list of breed items matching the specified criteria.

If no parameters are provided, returns a list of all breed items, paginated.

Parameters:

breed - (Optional) the specific breed you want information for

Return type:
```
dict {
	objects: [
		breed_dict_1,
		...
		breed_dict_12
	],
	page: number
}
```

query.description: (Required) The name of the specific breed.
(Optional) The current page (12 activities per page) of suitable activity information.

request.description:
Returns a list of activity items suitable for dogs of a specific breed, paginated.

'name' is required as a parameter.

Parameters:

name - (Required) The name of the specific breed.

page - (Optional) The current page (12 activities per page) of suitable activity information.

Return type:
```
dict {
	objects: [
		activity_dict_1,
		...
		activity_dict_12
	],
	page: number
}
```

            "description": "Come enjoy some "downward dog" time at our Yoga and Adoption event benefiting Braveheart Animal Rescue at the Downtown Arlington Farmer's Market!




Join Arlington Yoga Center, Union Worx Co-Working, and Braveheart Animal Rescue for an exciting afternoon full of giggles and licks...oh, and a little yoga!





Braveheart Animal Rescue will have a table set up, offering adoption services, answering any questions you have about their organization, as well as providing the adoptable dogs during our yoga class! 





This class will be held OUTDOORS (weather-permitting) and is family-friendly! 





Things to Know:

-The dogs will be provided for Pup Yoga, please leave yours at home!
-Though the title states Pup, our rescue organization will be providing small dogs of all ages and types. -Class will be open to all-levels

-BYOM (Bring your own mat and mat towel)


-Please register and purchase your ticket online before the day of the event


-Your ticket includes a free draft beer or drink from Legal Draft Beer


-While some yogis may take themselves (or their yoga practice) very seriously, pup yoga is for everyone and we welcome any and all participants. Remember we will be practicing with live animals, anything is possible!





We will definitely have time after the yoga class to snuggle, take pictures, and socialize with the dogs in case you want more!


After class feel free to head across the street to the Farmer's Market, grab your drink, and peruse all the homemade goods and produce from the market vendors!

It’s time for Goat Yoga with a purpose!  Join us at Bliss Fest in the beauiful Windsong Ranch in Prosper to support Lone Star Ranch and Rescue. 

We will be hosting 2 sessions of Goat Yoga and Playtime with the goats.  While we do charge for the Yoga sessions, playtime with the goats is free for all to enjoy, so bring your family and friends to enjoy the goats. This will be our first session of the season and it will be the first time our newest baby goats will make an appearance.
 
Goat Yoga is about disconnecting with day-to-day stress, sickness or depression and focusing on positive and happy vibes.  It is a time to enjoy these wonderful baby goats while supporting the efforts of Lone Star Ranch and Rescue, a horse rescue just outside of McKinney.
 
The Goat Yoga are hosted by Lone Star Ranch and Rescue (LSRR), a horse rescue based just minutes away from McKinney in beautiful Blue Ridge, Texas.  LSRR’s mission is to rescue, rehabilitate, and rehome horses and other farm animals.

The goats used for our yoga sessions are all bottle raised and people friendly.  These are not random rented  goats used to make a buck.  They are our pets and our friends.  We interact with them on a daily basis and make sure they have everything a goat could want and then some.  Feel free to come out to Lone Star and meet our friends.  Message us through Facebook to schedule some time.
Lone Star Ranch and Rescue is an IRS 501c3 charity with tax benefits for you when donating.

'name' is required as a parameter.

Parameters:

name - (Required) The name of the specific breed.

page - (Optional) The current page (12 dogs per page) of dog information.

Return type:
```
dict {
	objects: [
		dog_dict_1,
		...
		doct_dict_12
	],
	page: number
}
```

request.description:
Returns a list of breeds that match specfic filters. Can also use this method to sort results in a specific order.


Parameters:

group_filter - (Optional) The group that breed falls into. Valid inputs are "Mixed", "Working", "Non-Sporting", "Sporting", "Herding", "Terrier", "Hound", "Toy".

lifespan_filter - (Optional) The lifespan that you'd like to narrow breeds down by. Will return all breeds that have a lifespan range that includes the number you passed in. 

height_filter - (Optional) The height that you'd like to narrow breeds down by. Will return all breeds that have a height (in inches) that includes the number you passed in. 

search_param - (Optional) A string to search for in the breed list.

sort_param - (Optional) Possible sorts include "alphabetical", "reverse_alphabetical", "group", and "reverse_group"


Return type:
```
dict {
	objects: [
		breed_dict_1,
		...
		breed_dict_12
	],
	page: number
}
```

query.description: (Required) The ID of the activity.
(Optional) The range (in degrees) from the activity in which you want to find nearby dogs that would be suitable for this activity. The default is 0.5 degrees if no range is provided.

request.description:
Given an activity, returns a list of dog items representing dogs in nearby shelters that would be suitable for this activity within the specified range. This list is capped at 12 entries.

"id" is required as a parameter.

Parameters:

id - (Required) The ID of the activity.

range - (Optional) The range (in degrees) from the activity in which you want to find nearby dogs that would be suitable for this activity. The default is 0.5 degrees if no range is provided.

Return type:
```
dict {
	objects: [
		dog_dict_1,
		...
		dog_dict_12
	]
}
```

dict {

request.description:
Returns a list of activites that match specfic filters. Can also use this method to sort results in a specific order. 

Parameters:

active_filter - (Optional) "true" for active events, "false" for casual events.

free_filter - (Optional) "true" for free events, "false" for paid events. 

type_filter - (Optional) "eventbrite" for Eventbrite, "meetup" for Meetup, "park" for National Park.

search_param - (Optional) A string to search for in the activity list .

sort_param - (Optional) Possible sorts include "alphabetical", "reverse_alphabetical", "date", and "reverse_date"

page_num - (Optional) The page of results you'd like.

Return type:
```
dict {
	objects: [
		activity_dict_1,
		...
		activity_dict_12
	],
	page: number
}
```

We take in abandoned/homeless dogs and cats, get them healthy, and place them in foster homes where they can learn how to be a part of a loving family. All our animals are completely vetted, fixed, and micro chipped before joining their forever home. Our fosters help train and socialize our animals so they can be incorporated in their new family as quickly as possible.\"\n“Be Good . Do Good . Feel Good. **Did You Know** It's For Charity! Events are the creators of Happy Goat Yoga and many more fun activities throughout the Dallas - Fort Worth area?! The cool part is that every event is a fundraiser for a local non-profit focused on making the world a better place. For schedule of all events and locations, visit: www.itsforcharityevents.eventbrite.com and www.happygoatyoga.eventbrite.com \nFAQ\n1.       Is there an age requirement?   A. Unless specifically stated, our FUNdraiser events are family friendly. We welcome all well behaved children to join in on the happy-vibes. We just want to ensure all of our guests have a fun time.\n2.       Does my young child need a ticket?   A. If he/she is going to participate, yes. If he/she is going to share your mat, no.\n3.       I’m not into the yoga, but can I still come to play with the animals?   A. Yes! For many of participants, this is their first yoga experience. Many will sit and enjoy “cuddle” therapy throughout the class. No one is mad at that! You can also come for “Playtime Only” during the second hour. We only ask that you make a donation for the charity the event is benefiting when you arrive.\n4.       Do you have extra yoga mats?  A. We do have a few extra yoga mats at our events. They’re first come, first serve. We do recommend bringing your own if you have one. P.S. Have extras? Please donate them to us!\n5.       I am no longer able to  make it to the event, can I get a refund?    A. If its prior to the 7 day refund policy, yes. You will request a refund via Eventbrite, on the same page you bought your tickets. You also have the option to transfer your ticket to another date/event. Simply email us your request. If you are after the 7 day refund policy, no, we do not issue refunds. Instead, we will happily transfer your ticket(s) to another event we offer.\n6.       What happens if it rains?   A. We only call a class if/when rain looks definite. If we do get rained out, the event will be rescheduled. When any changes are made, all ticket holders will be emailed via Eventbrite to the email address associated to your tickets. We’ll also make a post on the Facebook Event Page. Make sure you’re following the page!\n7.       My event was rescheduled due to bad weather. The new date is inconvenient for me, can I have a refund?   A. We do not issue refunds due to rain outs. However, we will happily transfer your ticket(s) to another event we offer that is more convenient. If you don’t see a date that works for your schedule that is currently listed, we add new events every week. Once you see a convenient date, simply email us the new details and your tickets will be honored.\n8.       How does my company sponsor or host one of your events? A. Send us a message!
